  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-10-26T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Retirement Plan Modernization Act \n\nThis bill amends the Internal Revenue Code and the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (ERISA) to increase from $5,000 to $7,600 the amount of accrued benefits in a pension plan that may be immediately distributed without the consent of the participant. The bill also requires the increased limit to be adjusted for inflation after 2018."
